Hypopygium (
Figs. 29–33
, 
42
). Tergite IX without anal point, trapezoidal,densely covered with microtrichia, its free edge as it is curled inwards, in inner side and on the edge with middle and long 11–19 setae (
Fig. 31
). Laterosternite IX with 8–9 setae on each side. Transverse sternapodeme rounded, 108–112 µm long, with weak oral projections. Virga 40–48 µm long, consists of 2–3 colorless setae. Gonocoxite 260 µm long; inferior volsella as a rounded projection located in distal half of gonocoxite, covered with microtrichia and setae (
Figs. 29–30
). Gonostylus bifurcate, inner branch 104–108 µm long, with megaseta 14–20 µm long (
Figs. 29–30, 32
, 
42
).
